The '''Viral Hepatitis Congress''' is an [[academic conference]] aimed broadly at [[Gastroenterology|gastroenterologists]], [[Hepatology|hepatologists]], and specifically at [[viral hepatitis]]-treating clinicians and clinical researchers.
The inaugural Congress was held at the [[Goethe University|Goethe University Frankfurt]] from Friday 7 September to Sunday 9 September 2012.<ref>http://www.viral-hep.org/Page.aspx?Id=85</ref> In the region of 400 delegates, representing 43 countries, attended for the two and half day programme, featuring keynote lectures, plenary sessions and industry symposia. Scientific [[Abstract (summary)|abstracts]] were accepted to the Congress and presented as either [[Poster session|poster]] or oral communications, the abstracts presented at the meeting were published as a supplement to the ''Journal of Viral Hepatitis''.<ref>http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/jvh.2012.19.issue-s3/issuetoc</ref> In 2012<ref>http://www.eaccme.eu/eventlist.php?month=9&year=2012</ref> and 2013,<ref>http://www.eaccme.eu/eventlist.php?month=9&year=2013</ref> the Viral Hepatitis Congress was accredited by the European Accreditation Council for Continuing Medical Education (EACCME) and institution of the [[European Union of Medical Specialists]], and designated for up to 13 hours of European external [[Continuing medical education|CME]] credits.
The 2013 Congress took place at the [[Messe Frankfurt]] Congress Center from Thursday 26 September to Saturday 28 September 2013.<ref>http://www.messefrankfurt.com/content/corporate/frankfurt/en/besucher/welcome/kongresse.html</ref> Topics included:
* [[Hepatitis C]] Epidemiology, Screening and Diagnosis * The New Era of HCV Therapies: [[IFN]]-containing Regimens * The New Era of HCV Therapies: IFN-free Regimens * HCV Comorbidities * Clinical Challenges in Hepatitis C * [[Hepatitis B]] * [[Hepatitis D]] and [[Hepatitis E|E]] * [[Hepatocellular carcinoma]]
The abstracts presented at the 2013 Congress were again published as a supplement to the ''Journal of Viral Hepatitis''.<ref>http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/jvh.2013.20.issue-s3/issuetoc</ref>
The 2014 Congress will take place from Thursday 9 October to Saturday 11 October, in Frankfurt.
